Our company provides Agenda Management and Video Streaming to municipalities.  A meeting in our nomenclature is called an "Event" and contains one or more of the following:
- Agenda Items List (title, description, item attachments)
- Media (HLS-based playback of video and audio of the meeting)
- Attachment Media (available in the Agenda Area, but for the event itself and not a single agenda item)
- Timeline (links to offsets in the media file of the relevant sections)
- Minute Items (title / description [but mainly description] either tied to an agenda item or standalone that describe what happened during the meeting)

We have a few items of Jargon that we typically use:
- "MyDot" refers to the area where customers manipulate the events.  That is, it's the "platform" they interact with.
- "PlayDot" refers to there area where the public views things that the customer sets up on MyDot
- "Customer" and "Publisher" are used interchangibly and are synonymous

